claim.claim-text:
6. A method for producing a reinforcing coated metal wire of an elastomeric compound to be vulcanized, comprising: 
depositing on a metal wire alternate unalloyed layers of copper and zinc, a most external unalloyed layer being copper; 
selecting a thickness of the most external copper layer to obtain a desired copper concentration on an outer surface of the coated metal wire; 
drawing the metal wire with the alternate unalloyed layers to alloy the copper and zinc to form copper-based alloy; and 
combining the drawn coated wire with the elastomeric compound prior to vulcanization.
